00:11:41,750 --> 00:11:44,750
Then, make the Seal of the
Sword and focus your will.

268
00:11:44,833 --> 00:11:47,375
Naumaku san manda
bazaradan kan...

269
00:11:47,458 --> 00:11:50,166
Naumaku san manda
bazaradan kan.

270
00:11:52,666 --> 00:11:55,708
So... I don't know what
to think about Masako...

271
00:11:55,791 --> 00:11:57,500
She says she can't
see any spirits

272
00:11:57,583 --> 00:11:59,416
but she can sense
their presence...

273
00:11:59,500 --> 00:12:00,708
It's weird.

274
00:12:00,791 --> 00:12:04,000
Naru said she's one of
the best in Japan, right?

275
00:12:04,083 --> 00:12:07,416
Ya, but she seems
to be... off.

276
00:12:07,500 --> 00:12:09,083
But what about you, Mai...?

277
00:12:09,166 --> 00:12:10,666
Do you sense anything?

278
00:12:10,750 --> 00:12:12,000
Geez...

279
00:12:12,083 --> 00:12:13,541
You can't put me on
the spot like that.

280
00:12:13,625 --> 00:12:15,125
Remember earlier

281
00:12:15,208 --> 00:12:17,166
when I said there would be a
fire in the locker room...?

282
00:12:17,250 --> 00:12:18,416
You corrected me,

283
00:12:18,500 --> 00:12:20,291
saying it could be in
the announcement room.

284
00:12:20,375 --> 00:12:21,208
Really?

285
00:12:21,291 --> 00:12:22,708
Well I was taking a nap and ...

286
00:12:22,791 --> 00:12:25,041
It was in a dream I had.

287
00:12:25,125 --> 00:12:25,875
A dream.

288
00:12:27,541 --> 00:12:29,083
I see.

289
00:12:29,166 --> 00:12:30,166
Like I told you...

290
00:12:30,250 --> 00:12:31,916
It was just a
stupid dream.

291
00:12:33,041 --> 00:12:35,541
Ok Mia be a good
girl and sleep.

292
00:12:35,625 --> 00:12:37,375
I'm not tired, Monk!

293
00:12:37,458 --> 00:12:39,500
Whether you like it or not,
your dreams have meaning.

294
00:12:39,583 --> 00:12:41,125
This is purely for
collecting information.

295
00:12:41,208 --> 00:12:42,958
Now sleep!

296
00:12:43,041 --> 00:12:45,666
Masako and Ayako did exorcise
the locker room earlier

297
00:12:45,750 --> 00:12:47,375
so, maybe you're
on to something.

298
00:12:47,458 --> 00:12:48,500
Come on...

299
00:12:48,583 --> 00:12:50,000
It's just a coincidence!

300
00:12:50,083 --> 00:12:51,708
Don't try to
play it off Mai.

301
00:12:51,791 --> 00:12:54,041
You've had dreams before
that related to a case.

302
00:12:54,125 --> 00:12:56,125
You want me to go to
sleep right on cue?

303
00:12:56,208 --> 00:12:57,333
Now now...

304
00:12:57,416 --> 00:12:59,958
We'll find out if Mai's
right soon enough.

305
00:13:00,041 --> 00:13:01,833
If there is a fire in
the announcement room,

306
00:13:01,916 --> 00:13:04,500
then it will prove that
Mai's dreams have relevance.

307
00:13:04,583 --> 00:13:06,500
And if she does
end up being correct,

308
00:13:06,583 --> 00:13:07,750
I'd like to see
her more involved

309
00:13:07,833 --> 00:13:10,458
in the case-solving process.

310
00:13:10,541 --> 00:13:13,666
Since when have you been
Mai's personal manager?

311
00:13:13,750 --> 00:13:15,333
Since now.

312
00:13:15,416 --> 00:13:17,000
You two keep trying
to one up each other

313
00:13:17,083 --> 00:13:20,458
like you're related.

314
00:13:20,541 --> 00:13:23,333
I'm tired of him running his
mouth about whatever he wants.

315
00:13:23,416 --> 00:13:25,083
Just because I've been
right in the past

316
00:13:25,166 --> 00:13:27,000
doesn't mean it'll
come true this time.

317
00:13:28,291 --> 00:13:29,791
But later that night,

318
00:13:29,875 --> 00:13:31,458
or more accurately,
the next morning

319
00:13:31,541 --> 00:13:33,791
at four-thirty-two a.m...

320
00:13:33,875 --> 00:13:35,500
that's exactly
what happened.

321
00:13:54,666 --> 00:13:56,583
What did I tell you Mai?

322
00:13:56,666 --> 00:13:58,083
I don't believe this.

323
00:13:58,166 --> 00:13:59,541
I was right.

324
00:13:59,625 --> 00:14:02,375
I never really thought
it would actually happen.

325
00:14:02,458 --> 00:14:04,125
I mean I'm glad that I'm
able to help besides

326
00:14:04,208 --> 00:14:07,500
just being a gopher
all the time, but...

327
00:14:07,583 --> 00:14:10,250
Still... This is more damage
than we've heard of before...

328
00:14:10,333 --> 00:14:12,375
It did more than
scorch the walls.

329
00:14:12,458 --> 00:14:14,041
Yeah I've never
seen it this bad.

330
00:14:14,125 --> 00:14:16,625
Where else are the
foxfires supposed to be?

331
00:14:16,708 --> 00:14:18,166
Let's... see...

332
00:14:18,250 --> 00:14:20,958
The printing room,
the language lab...

333
00:14:21,041 --> 00:14:23,375
and the nurse's office
were the bigger ones...

334
00:14:23,458 --> 00:14:24,375
But...

335
00:14:24,458 --> 00:14:25,625
But what?

336
00:14:25,708 --> 00:14:27,666
The chance that I know
is pretty slim, right?

337
00:14:27,750 --> 00:14:29,666
I'm not counting on
you all that much.

338
00:14:29,750 --> 00:14:31,750
Yeah... I wouldn't
expect you to?

339
00:14:31,833 --> 00:14:33,791
I've got some
bad news Naru.

340
00:14:33,875 --> 00:14:35,708
It looks like your
camera here is toast.

341
00:14:35,791 --> 00:14:37,583
Oh... That's alright...

342
00:14:37,666 --> 00:14:39,041
Insurance covers it.

343
00:14:39,125 --> 00:14:40,541
Wait, it does?

344
00:14:42,875 --> 00:14:45,958
Naru! Remember when you
asked me to be your assistant

345
00:14:46,041 --> 00:14:47,500
because I could never
afford to pay you back

346
00:14:47,583 --> 00:14:49,333
for the camera I broke?

347
00:14:49,416 --> 00:14:51,166
Did you tell me that just

348
00:14:51,250 --> 00:14:52,916
so you could get some
free help out of me...?

349
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:54,625
Promise you'll
tell the truth.

350
00:14:58,208 --> 00:15:00,791
You're getting smarter
and smarter every day.

351
00:15:02,833 --> 00:15:03,750
Why you...?!

352
00:15:03,833 --> 00:15:05,833
How dare you trick me!!...!

353
00:15:05,916 --> 00:15:07,208
Mai, he's not worth it!

354
00:15:07,291 --> 00:15:09,500
NARU!

355
00:15:09,583 --> 00:15:12,375
I can't believe he took
advantage of me like that.

356
00:15:12,458 --> 00:15:13,416
Sure, I'll admit it.

357
00:15:13,500 --> 00:15:14,916
I was naïve back then,

358
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:17,083
but the least he could
do is be honest...

359
00:15:17,166 --> 00:15:19,166
Though he did give
me a really cool job.

360
00:15:20,458 --> 00:15:22,291
Hey you.

361
00:15:22,375 --> 00:15:23,708
Are you people done yet?

362
00:15:23,791 --> 00:15:25,583
Ugh, not him again.

363
00:15:25,666 --> 00:15:27,833
I heard there was another
fire this morning...

364
00:15:27,916 --> 00:15:30,541
I guess your silly little
exorcisms didn't take.

365
00:15:30,625 --> 00:15:31,916
Well, uh, sir...

366
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:33,708
The main problem
with you people

367
00:15:33,791 --> 00:15:35,666
is the only place
ghosts exist...

368
00:15:35,750 --> 00:15:37,458
is in your imaginations.

369
00:15:37,541 --> 00:15:40,458
You exploit weak-minded
people to earn a buck.

370
00:15:40,541 --> 00:15:41,666
Excuse me sir,

371
00:15:41,750 --> 00:15:43,833
but I really need to
get back to work now.

372
00:15:43,916 --> 00:15:45,375
Would you like to know
what happens to those

373
00:15:45,458 --> 00:15:47,458
who ignore their studies
by wasting their time

374
00:15:47,541 --> 00:15:49,500
with this occult nonsense?

375
00:15:49,583 --> 00:15:51,208
It happened to a
student of ours.

376
00:15:51,291 --> 00:15:53,541
He became so obsessed with
the dark side of life

377
00:15:53,625 --> 00:15:55,291
it eventually lead
to his demise.

378
00:15:55,375 --> 00:15:56,625
Yes sir...

379
00:15:56,708 --> 00:15:58,583
We're aware of what
happened to Sakauchi.

380
00:15:58,666 --> 00:16:00,166
Is that right...?

381
00:16:00,250 --> 00:16:03,250
Watch out that you don't
end up just like him...

382
00:16:03,333 --> 00:16:04,791
I'm sure he's regretting

383
00:16:04,875 --> 00:16:06,333
what he did in
the afterlife.

384
00:16:08,125 --> 00:16:10,708
He's had some kind
of bad experience

385
00:16:10,791 --> 00:16:12,958
happen at this school.

386
00:16:13,041 --> 00:16:14,708
So if I understand
you correctly,

387
00:16:14,791 --> 00:16:16,291
you're basically not sorry

388
00:16:16,375 --> 00:16:18,291
for what happened to
your student, are you sir?

389
00:16:18,375 --> 00:16:19,666
What...?

390
00:16:19,750 --> 00:16:21,416
I never said
any such thing.

391
00:16:21,500 --> 00:16:23,958
Well I'm sorry but that sure
is the way it sounded to me.

392
00:16:27,666 --> 00:16:28,791
Mai what's going on?

393
00:16:28,875 --> 00:16:30,166
Uh, I don't know!

394
00:16:39,666 --> 00:16:41,166
It smells awful!

395
00:16:41,250 --> 00:16:43,208
Could that be the
same dog as last time?

396
00:16:47,916 --> 00:16:49,000
Mai, careful!

397
00:16:59,250 --> 00:17:01,333
I've never encountered
a spirit like that...

398
00:17:01,416 --> 00:17:03,750
It's as if it had
physical substance.

399
00:17:05,916 --> 00:17:08,166
Excuse me... Excuse me...

400
00:17:08,250 --> 00:17:09,416
Matsuyama!

401
00:17:09,500 --> 00:17:10,500
Huh?

402
00:17:10,583 --> 00:17:12,250
You need to call
an ambulance ...

403
00:17:12,333 --> 00:17:13,958
We have some injured
students here.

404
00:17:15,625 --> 00:17:16,875
So... was that the same dog

405
00:17:16,958 --> 00:17:18,666
we had a run in
with yesterday?

406
00:17:18,750 --> 00:17:21,875
If it was then it's grown
since we saw it last.

407
00:17:21,958 --> 00:17:23,708
It must be
getting stronger.

408
00:17:27,958 --> 00:17:29,750
Masako...!
Are you okay?

409
00:17:31,083 --> 00:17:32,583
What's wrong?

410
00:17:36,375 --> 00:17:37,916
What the...

411
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:39,250
It's happening again.

412
00:17:41,958 --> 00:17:44,750
It's just like in
my dream yesterday.

413
00:17:44,833 --> 00:17:46,708
No, get away from it!

414
00:17:46,791 --> 00:17:48,458
If you get too close
you'll get eaten!

415
00:17:50,541 --> 00:17:52,583
Oh my god...

416
00:17:52,666 --> 00:17:54,208
is that...

417
00:17:54,291 --> 00:17:55,250
Sakauchi?!

418
00:18:02,458 --> 00:18:03,500
It is him.

419
00:18:15,666 --> 00:18:17,333
Are you two okay?

420
00:18:19,541 --> 00:18:20,500
What happened...?

421
00:18:20,583 --> 00:18:22,041
The two of you
just fainted...

422
00:18:22,125 --> 00:18:24,583
It scared us.

423
00:18:24,666 --> 00:18:27,083
I take it you saw it too.

424
00:18:27,166 --> 00:18:28,333
Yes.

425
00:18:28,416 --> 00:18:30,083
Sakauchi's gone...

426
00:18:30,166 --> 00:18:31,583
He disappeared.

427
00:18:33,708 --> 00:18:36,458
It's exactly like what
happened in Mai's dream.

428
00:18:36,541 --> 00:18:39,333
The spirits have now begun
to consume each other...

429
00:18:39,416 --> 00:18:40,750
Sakauchi...

430
00:18:40,833 --> 00:18:42,500
He was absorbed
by another.

431
00:18:42,583 --> 00:18:43,833
Hold on...

432
00:18:43,916 --> 00:18:46,958
So any spirit we drive out
isn't being exorcised...

433
00:18:47,041 --> 00:18:48,708
It just flees to
another location

434
00:18:48,791 --> 00:18:50,791
where it's eaten by another,
bigger spirit?

435
00:18:50,875 --> 00:18:52,166
And then the spirits

436
00:18:52,250 --> 00:18:54,333
that cannibalize the others
become stronger...

437
00:18:54,416 --> 00:18:56,833
It's quite frightening.

438
00:18:56,916 --> 00:19:00,125
And I thought it was
all just a dream...

439
00:19:00,208 --> 00:19:03,000
If this continues
to escalate, then...

440
00:19:03,083 --> 00:19:05,375
So what do you
think we should do?

441
00:19:05,458 --> 00:19:09,250
It may be wise to hold off
on the exorcisms for now...

442
00:19:09,333 --> 00:19:10,583
There's no telling
what will happen

443
00:19:10,666 --> 00:19:12,583
if they run off this time.

444
00:19:12,666 --> 00:19:14,125
This is getting worse

445
00:19:15,500 --> 00:19:16,791
Umm... Excuse me.

446
00:19:16,875 --> 00:19:19,125
What is it?

447
00:19:19,208 --> 00:19:21,875
I heard something that
was a little disturbing.

448
00:19:21,958 --> 00:19:23,375
And what's that?

449
00:19:23,458 --> 00:19:24,958
Well...

450
00:19:25,041 --> 00:19:28,125
I traced back to the first use
of orikirisama in the school.

451
00:19:28,208 --> 00:19:29,875
My conversation
with Mai yesterday

452
00:19:29,958 --> 00:19:31,125
got me thinking...

453
00:19:31,208 --> 00:19:33,000
It looks like the
orikirisama fad

454
00:19:33,083 --> 00:19:36,333
began shortly after
the second semester.

455
00:19:36,416 --> 00:19:38,083
There were two groups...

456
00:19:38,166 --> 00:19:39,750
The freshman class
and the art club,

457
00:19:39,833 --> 00:19:43,666
and it seems they both started
using it at the same time...

458
00:19:43,750 --> 00:19:45,041
But there's more
to it than that.

459
00:19:45,125 --> 00:19:47,333
And unfortunately
it's worse.

460
00:19:47,416 --> 00:19:50,208
Not only was Sakauchi a
member of the art club...

461
00:19:50,291 --> 00:19:52,750
But he was also a
freshman at the time...

462
00:19:52,833 --> 00:19:54,791
Now I'm not drawing any
conclusions from this,

463
00:19:54,875 --> 00:19:56,291
but it is interesting...

464
00:19:56,375 --> 00:19:58,833
It definitely seems like
it could be relevant.

465
00:19:58,916 --> 00:20:00,916
Although it's an
interesting development...

466
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:02,333
It doesn't change the fact

467
00:20:02,416 --> 00:20:04,666
that the practice spread
through the school...

468
00:20:04,750 --> 00:20:06,708
Countless séances
took place

469
00:20:06,791 --> 00:20:09,541
and spirits were summoned
as a direct result...

470
00:20:09,625 --> 00:20:12,208
However there's still
a piece missing.

471
00:20:12,291 --> 00:20:13,916
Something strange
and nefarious

472
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:15,416
is happening in
this school...

473
00:20:15,500 --> 00:20:18,125
Regardless of how many
séances were performed...

474
00:20:18,208 --> 00:20:20,000
I seriously doubt
amateurs could summon

475
00:20:20,083 --> 00:20:22,416
such a large
amount of spirits.

476
00:20:22,500 --> 00:20:25,041
So, what now...

477
00:20:25,125 --> 00:20:26,375
This is a tough one.

478
00:20:29,041 --> 00:20:30,833
What was I thinking?

479
00:20:30,916 --> 00:20:32,875
I should have had someone
else come with me...

480
00:20:32,958 --> 00:20:34,708
This school is the
creepiest place

481
00:20:34,791 --> 00:20:36,458
in the world at night.

482
00:20:36,541 --> 00:20:39,250
I'm just waiting for a
monster to jump out at me.

483
00:20:39,333 --> 00:20:42,916
C'mon... Just stay focused
and it'll all be okay...

484
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:45,291
All I need to do is get the
tape and head back to base.

485
00:20:48,083 --> 00:20:51,000
Cool, I'll just
grab this and go.

486
00:20:51,083 --> 00:20:53,541
Uh. Oh man...

487
00:20:53,625 --> 00:20:56,333
Naru's gonna kill
me if I broke it...

488
00:20:56,416 --> 00:20:58,083
What? You've got
to be kidding me.

489
00:20:58,166 --> 00:20:59,333
A power outage...?

490
00:20:59,416 --> 00:21:02,541
Talk about bad timing.

491
00:21:02,625 --> 00:21:05,583
A power outage wouldn't
affect my flashlight...

492
00:21:05,666 --> 00:21:08,000
I've got a bad
feeling about this.

493
00:21:08,083 --> 00:21:10,500
I'm just gonna turn around
and head back to base.

494
00:21:13,500 --> 00:21:15,458
Come on, door!
Open already...

495
00:21:15,541 --> 00:21:17,416
There isn't even a
lock on this thing.

496
00:21:23,750 --> 00:21:25,000
Children?

497
00:21:25,083 --> 00:21:26,583
What are they doing here?

498
00:21:26,666 --> 00:21:28,291
It's the middle
of the night.

499
00:21:28,375 --> 00:21:29,250
Unless they're...

500
00:21:49,083 --> 00:21:51,041
That smells like
formaldehyde...

501
00:21:51,125 --> 00:21:52,583
Where is it coming from?

502
00:21:58,250 --> 00:21:59,958
Somebody! Help me!

503
00:22:00,041 --> 00:22:01,541
Let me out...!

504
00:22:01,625 --> 00:22:04,708
Please somebody help me!

505
00:22:04,791 --> 00:22:06,916
Please... help... me.

506
00:22:17,416 --> 00:22:23,125
[Music]

507
00:23:49,750 --> 00:23:53,291
Next time on Ghost Hunt,
Forbidden Pastime Part Three!

508
00:23:53,375 --> 00:23:54,833
Are you freaked out yet?

